dcterms:description: The Cognitive Psychology Probe Data consists of 150 images of objects arranged in triples, including a probe image, a shape-match image, and a color-match image. The dataset is designed to control for background content and object size, and it is used to test the shape bias in deep neural networks.
dcterms:title: Cognitive Psychology Probe Data (CogPsyc data)

dcterms:description: A real-world dataset consisting of 90 images of objects collected using Google Image Search, arranged in triples similar to the CogPsyc dataset. This dataset aims to probe the models' properties outside of the image space covered in standard datasets like ImageNet.
dcterms:title: Probe Data from the wild
